2.10	Solly_Tyibilika	Solly Tyibilika	Solomzi "Solly" Tyibilika (23 June 1979 â€“ 13 November 2011) was a South African rugby union footballer, who played as a flanker for the Lions in the international Super 14 competition in his last years. He was the first black person (not white or mixed race) to score a test try for the South Africa national rugby union team.	
